"Life is only precious because it ends, kid. Take it from a god. You mortals don't know how lucky you are\n\n- Rick Riordan, The Son of Neptune\n|\nLosing someone you love is harder. One minute they're there, the next they're gone. There were times I wished they would rise up from the dead.\n\n- Denise Grover Swank, Chosen\n|\nThe man is happiest who lives from day to day and asks no more, garnering the simple goodness of life.\n\n- Euripides\n|\nTo work best democracy needs a diversity of thoughts, ideas and expression. This is only possible with freedom and civility.\n\n- Kevin\n|\nLife is a compromise of what your ego wants to do, what experience tells you to do, and what your nerves let you do.\n\n- Walter\n|\nI cannot pretend that I regard this with favor, but the purpose of life is not to do what we want but what needs to be done. This is what fate demands of us. - Oromis\n\n- Christopher Paolini, Brisingr\n|\nOnce, I remember, Father Abbot said that our purpose is justice, and with God lies the privilege of mercy. But even God, when he intends mercy, needs tools to his hand.\n\n- Ellis Peters, Dead Man's Ransom\n|\nAh, ye brethren, that God whom I created was human work and human madness, like all the Gods!\n\n- Friedrich Nietzsche, Thus Spoke Zarathustra\n|\nI think books are like people, in the sense that they'll turn up in your life when you most need them.\n\n- Emma\n|\nEven the worst days have an ending, and the best days have a beginning.\n\n- Jennifer\n|\nYes, King Edward VI lived only a few years, poor boy, but he lived them worthily.\n\n- Mark Twain, The Prince and the Pauper\n|\nIf the management has not performed well in their bad times in the past, chances are they will not perform well in their good times in the future too.\n\n- Vijay\n|\nI will follow you, my love, to the edge of all our days,to our very last tomorrows.\n\n- Atticus Poetry, Love Her Wild: Poems\n|\nI have hope for you, if only because you're the only one left to hope for.\n\n- Orson Scott Card, Ender's Game\n|\nAre you going to answer my questions, or do I have to whack you with a stick until delicious candy surprises fall out?\n\n- Molly Harper, Nice Girls Don't Have Fangs\n|\nEveryone just wasting time because they have so much of it to waste, minutes slipping by on who's with who and did you hear.\n\n- Lauren Oliver, Before I Fall\n|\nYou might be educated, but if you are not kind you are not wise.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nFor you not to waste or spend your life, you must first understand that time is life and life is time.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nAmerica... goes not abroad, in search of monsters to destroy. She is the well-wisher to the freedom and independence of all.\n\n- John\n|\nThe purpose of influence is to 'speak up for those who have no influence.' (Pr.31:8) It's not about you.\n\n- Rick\n|\nMy spirit is joyful, and I love my higher self. I am my higher self.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, Joyful Living: 101 Ways to Transform Your Spirit and Revitalize Your Life\n|\nEven if it was just walls and a roof with papers inside, it had bewitched him, and drawn him in, and given him everything he needed to become himself.\n\n- Laini Taylor, Strange the Dreamer\n|\nI came only to report the news, to gather information. I didn't come to find out the truth.\n\n- Siriworn Kaewkan, The Murder Case of Tok Imam Storpa Karde\n|\nJust because you're beautiful and perfect, it's made you conceited.\n\n- William Goldman, The Princess Bride\n|\nThat is how we become wise, by living each day attending to the lessons God puts in our path.\n\n- Emma Campion, The King's Mistress\n|\nThe good is the Enemy of the best. Until you depart from the good, you cannot enter God's best for your life.\n\n- Pedro Okoro, Crushing the Devil: Your Guide to Spiritual Warfare and Victory in Christ\n|\nColonial power, patriarchal power, capitalist power must always and everywhere be battled, because they never, ever quit. (Junot Diaz)\n\n- Carolina De Robertis, Radical Hope: Letters of Love and Dissent in Dangerous Times\n|\nLife is like a storm. At its worst, it's full of blinding fury, rage, and destruction. However, at its best, it is full of striking beauty and wonder.\n\n- Tanner\n|\nFundamentalism's strident denunciation of its opponents is a sign of its weakness, its dogmatic authoritarianism is a pathological mutation of faith.\n\n- Alan\n|\nThere is no greater poverty, than poverty of the mind.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nJesus, Morelli, you sound like you have PMS. You have to learn to lighten up a little. It's just a car alarm. You should be thanking me. I had it installed with my own money.\n\n- Janet Evanovich, One for the Money\n|\nWhen we are connected to the source, we will not be afraid of any task set before us.\n\n- Jaachynma N.E. Agu, The Prince and the Pauper\n|\nWithout order in your life, you will realize that you will only be busy but without commensurate results.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nIt’s never wrong to be rich, but I want to believe, success is not limited to riches; it involves influence. If your riches don't create any impact, you are missing it.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Leaders' Frontpage: Leadership Insights from 21 Martin Luther King Jr. Thoughts\n|\nI have always considered 'Pascal's Wager' a questionable bet to place, since any God worth believing in would prefer an honest agnostic to a calculating hypocrite.\n\n- Alan M. Dershowitz, Letters to a Young Lawyer (Art of Mentoring\n|\nI realized then that even though I was a tiny speck in an infinite cosmos, a blip on the timeline of eternity, I was not without purpose.\n\n- R.J. Anderson, Ultraviolet\n|\nSince time comes in seconds, in minutes and in hours, we must learn to convert time, else, it will slip away and can never be regained.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nI had heard of Virginia before only in passing, a 'crazy ex' with whom things had not ended well. I was accustomed to this lazy shorthand for men who dislike the emotions of women.\n\n- Alana Massey, All the Lives I Want: Essays About My Best Friends Who Happen to Be Famous Strangers\n|\nIt’s true that no one ever said life would be easy, but it is also true that no one ever said you had to go through it alone.\n\n- Jellis\n|\nOh, wearisome condition of humanity,Born under one law, to another bound;Vainly begot, and yet forbidden vanity,Created sick, commanded to be sound.\n\n- Fulke\n|\nNever marry when under the guise you need to 'see if it'll work', but rather marry because in your mind you want to make it work.\n\n- Criss\n|\nDo not stop thinking of life as an adventure. You have no security unless you can live bravely, excitingly, imaginatively; unless you can choose a challenge instead of competence.\n\n- Eleanor Roosevelt, The Autobiography of Eleanor Roosevelt\n|\nWith time, many staged photographs turn back into historical evidence, albeit of an impure kind - like most historical evidence.\n\n- Susan Sontag, Regarding the Pain of Others\n|\nExperience has shown, and a true philosophy will always show, that a vast, perhaps the larger, portion of truth arises from the seemingly irrelevant.\n\n- Edgar Allan Poe, The Mystery of Marie Rogêt\n|\nAh, life's little surprises! They can make any day unforgettable... or make it your last.\n\n- T.A.\n|\nKnowledge is a destination. Truth, the journey.\n\n- Terry\n|\nYou know what they say about hope, it breeds eternal misery\n\n- Spencer\n|\nGod gave you a special purpose, do not see yourself as insignificant\n\n- Sunday\n|\nYou are all alike, you people. You never learn the truth--that God knows nothing.\n\n- Graham Greene, The Power and the Glory\n|\nDon't be afraid of death; be afraid of an unlived life. You don't have to live forever, you just have to live.\n\n- Natalie Babbitt, Tuck Everlasting\n|\nThe proper, wise balancingof one's whole life may depend upon thefeasibility of a cup of tea at an unusual hour.\n\n- Arnold Bennett, How to Live on 24 Hours a Day\n|\nBlackmailers never explain their thinking. They're like pirates that way. Dark-hearted, dangerous--- and cool like Johnny Depp.\n\n- Janette Rallison, How to Take the Ex Out of Ex-Boyfriend\n|\nKnowledge is power. The moment the masses acquire this power, control fades. And when control fades, chaos erupts.\n\n- Felix O. Hartmann, Dark Age\n|\nUntil you commit your goals to paper, you have intentions that are seeds without soil.\n\n- Unknown\n|\nTry, reach, want, and you may fall. But even if you do, you might be okay anyway. If you don't try, you save nothing, because you might as well be dead.\n\n- Ann Brashares, Girls in Pants: The Third Summer of the Sisterhood\n|\nA business is like an automobile. Its people its wheels, their passion its fuel.\n\n- Ajeet Sharma, Three Marketeers\n|\nThough all men be equally frail before the world, the differences between them are terrifying.\n\n- R. Scott Bakker, The Darkness That Comes Before\n|\nAh, young love. I will miss seeing how this unfolds.' -DezPierre\n\n- Jackie Castle, Emanate\n|\nAh, heavens and earth, friend, if you had made the acquiring of ignorance the study of your life, you could not have graduated with higher honor that you could to-day.\n\n- Mark Twain, Collected Tales, Sketches, Speeches & Essays, 2 Vols\n|\nWriting is storytelling and all of us are authors, not just of words but of reality. You are the author of your life, so go out and live! Then never quit writing about it!\n\n- Ben\n|\nThe Good News does not hinge on words like do or change but on the powerless, irrelevant, and frightening words like belief and faith.\n\n- Mark Galli, Chaos and Grace: Discovering the Liberating Work of the Holy Spirit\n|\nWhat should I get from books?” Alcide asked in French.That you are not alone — even along this broken tractor road. You need to know nothing else,” my father answered in French.\n\n- David Adams Richards, Mercy Among the Children\n|\nYour life - and all lives - will be richer if lived with a open, loving heart rather than a closed, fearful mind\n\n- Rasheed\n|\nShe'd always been a little excitable, a little more passionate about books than your average person, but she was supposed to be -- she was a librarian, after all.\n\n- Sarah\n|\nOur ancestors sought knowledge, but we, their descendants, glorify ignorance.\n\n- S.J. Kincaid, The Diabolic\n|\nMastery is the breeding ground of fresh, creative passion.\n\n- Mollie\n|\nExpectations make people miserable, so whatever yours are, lower them. You'll definitely be happier.\n\n- Simone Elkeles, How to Ruin Your Boyfriend's Reputation\n|\nThere is one who remembers the way to your door: Life you may evade, but Death you shall not.\n\n- T.S.\n|\nIt is not always a problem finding the truth, it is however sometimes a problem accepting it.\n\n- sunny-drunk\n|\nNot only is the Universe stranger than we think, it is stranger than we can think.\n\n- Werner Heisenberg, Across the Frontiers\n|\nI am not an optimist, but a great believer of hope.\n\n- Nelson\n|\nEveryone has too much of something, whether it’s time, talent or treasure. Everyone does have their own half, you just have to find it.\n\n- Hannah Salwen, The Power of Half: One Family's Decision to Stop Taking and Start Giving Back\n|\nIf you can't talk about, write about it!\n\n- Tracey\n|\nFaith, in the sense in which I am here using the word, is the art of holding on to things your reason has once accepted, in spite of your changing moods.\n\n- C.S. Lewis, Mere Christianity\n|\nOn the inner side of the aquarium of reality, beliefs define the area of the prison.\n\n- Robert Neil Fleischer, Alien Biography\n|\nThis book taught me, once and for all, how easily you can escape this world with the help of words! You can find friends between the pages of a book, wonderful friends.\n\n- Cornelia Funke, Inkspell\n|\nIf you can't be honest with your friends and colleagues and loved ones, then what is life all about?\n\n- Sophie Kinsella, Can You Keep a Secret?\n|\nIsabelle says the Queen of the Seelie Court has requested an audience with is'Sure' said Magnus. 'And Madonna wants me as a backup dancer on her next world tour\n\n- Cassandra\n|\nIf you want to use television to teach somebody, you must first teachthem how to use television.\n\n- Umberto\n|\nA doctor may know more than a peasant, but a peasant and a doctor know more together.\n\n- Dan Buettner, Thrive: Finding Happiness the Blue Zones Way\n|\nAlways take a compliment, Caroline. Always take it for the way it was intended. You girls are always so quick to twist what others say. Simply say thank you and move on.\n\n- Alice Clayton, Wallbanger\n|\nIf God spoke from Heaven, people will not understand Him, that is why Jesus came to earth\n\n- Sunday\n|\nSo do we discover, in the world, that our worst fears are unfulfilled; yet we must fear, in order that we may feel delight.\n\n- Peter Ackroyd, English Music\n|\nI don't know how I look, but I know how I feel: Young. Goofy. Infinite.\n\n- John Green, Paper Towns\n|\nThe boundaries we erect to divide heaven from earth, mind from matter, real from unreal are mere conveniences. Having made the boundaries, we can unmake them just as easily.\n\n- Deepak Chopra, The Way of the Wizard: Twenty Spiritual Lessons for Creating the Life You Want\n|\nYou need to maximize your Gods given potential through the power of your spirit, your inner core, your values and principles on which your life is based\n\n- Sunday\n|\nAll alone in an unfamiliar place, like some solitary explorer who's lost his compass and his map. Is this what it means to be free?\n\n- Haruki Murakami, Kafka on the Shore\n|\nBefore speaking, consult your inner-truth barometer, and resist the temptation to tell people only what they want to hear.\n\n- Wayne\n|\nImpossible things are really rough to do, you know.\n\n- Brandon Sanderson, Alcatraz Versus the Shattered Lens\n|\nIt's a reflex. Hear a bell, get food. See an undead, throw a knife. Same thing, really.\n\n- Ilona Andrews, Magic Bites\n|\nWords are directed to your personalities namely; - God, your hearers, devil and yourself.\n\n- Jaachynma N.E. Agu, The Prince and the Pauper\n|\nFear? What has a man to do with fear? Chance rules our lives, and the future is all unknown. Best live as we may, from day to day.\n\n- Sophocles, Oedipus Rex\n|\nI NAME THIS LAND TOMORROW, FOR IT SHALL LAST FOREVERMORE!\n\n- Cressida Cowell, How to Break a Dragon's Heart\n|\nHope just means another world might be possible, not promise, not guaranteed. Hope calls for action; action is impossible without hope.\n\n- Rebecca Solnit, Hope in the Dark\n|\nMaybe we were all destined to just keep doing the same stupid things, over and over again, never really learning a single thing.\n\n- Sarah Dessen, Along for the Ride\n|\nYou see, nothing matters except pleasure - which is the opposite of happiness, its tragic part, I expect.\n\n- Lawrence Durrell, The Alexandria Quartet\n|\nWhen a day goes by and I haven't written anything, I better have been doing something worth writing about.\n\n- P.S.\n|\nA simple 'Hi' has potential to make you blush, if received from your crush ...\n\n- Vergi\n|\nShe smiled smugly. “We came to an agreement, the duck and I.\n\n- Cassandra Clare, Clockwork Angel\n|\nFear is the bane of all creatures that bubbles inside us forming rocks of resistence, sucking away all will power to act, think or speak.\n\n- Isabella"